---
scientific_name: Glycine max
gene_symbols:
  - GmRhg1
  - GmSNAP18
gene_symbol_long: Soluble NSF Attachment Protein 18
gene_model_pub_name: Glyma.18G022500
gene_model_full_id: glyma.Wm82.gnm2.ann1.Glyma.18G022500
confidence: 5
curators:
  - Ella Townsend
  - Scott Kalberer
comments:
  - GmSNAP18 interactions with alleles of GmSHMT08 proteins determine reaction specificity to SCN (soybean cyst nematode) HG types.
  - Increased GmSNAP18 expression was observed in SCN-infected root tissue.
  - Molecular mechanism for SCN resistance by these two genes is not yet fully revealed.
phenotype_synopsis: Response to soybean cyst nematode infection as well as "Peking-type" resistance.
traits:
  - entity_name: Heterodera glycines response
    entity: TO:0001111
  - entity_name: Response to nematode
    entity: GO:0009624
  - entity_name: Defense response to nematode
    entity: GO:0002215
