scientific_name: Glycine max
gene_symbols:
  - GmRhg4
  - GmSHMT08
gene_symbol_long: Serine Hydroxymethyltransferase 8
gene_model_pub_name: Glyma.08g108900
gene_model_full_id: glyma.Wm82.gnm2.ann1.Glyma.08g108900
confidence: 5
curators:
  - Ella Townsend
  - Scott Kalberer
comments:
  - GmSHMT08 interactions with alleles of GmSNAP18 proteins determine reaction specificity to SCN (soybean cyst nematode) HG types.
  - GmSHMT08 functions downstream of the GmSNAP18 gene and its induction requires the presence of both functional GmSNAP18 resistant and GmSHMT08 resistant alleles.
  - Molecular mechanism for SCN resistance by these two genes is not yet fully revealed.
phenotype_synopsis: Response to soybean cyst nematode infection and "Peking-type" resistance.
traits:
  - entity_name: Heterodera glycines response
    entity: TO:0001111
  - entity_name: Response to nematode
    entity: GO:0009624
  - entity_name: Defense response to nematode
    entity: GO:0002215
references:
  - citation: Lakhssassi, Piya et al., 2020
    doi: 10.1111/pbi.13343
    pmid: 31960590
  - citation: Chaiprom, Miraeiz et al., 2024
    doi: 10.1093/g3journal/jkae226
    pmid: 39295536
  - citation: Guo, Zhang et al., 2019
    doi: 10.1111/mpp.12753
    pmid: 30264924
  - citation: Butler, Chen et al., 2019
